-- U.S. Eliminates Federer, Switzerland After Davis Cup Doubles; Spain Wins
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-02-11T18:11:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-11/u-s-eliminates-federer-switzerland-after-davis-cup-doubles-spain-wins.html
The U.S. eliminated  Switzerland  in
the first round of tennis’s Davis Cup, as defending champion
Spain advanced.  Mike Bryan and Mardy Fish defeated Roger Federer and
Stanislas Wawrinka 4-6, 6-3, 6-3, 6-3 to give the U.S. an
unbeatable 3-0 lead in the best-of-five series in Fribourg,
Switzerland. John Isner beat Federer and Fish defeated Wawrinka
in yesterday’s opening singles matches.  Spain took a 3-0 lead over Kazakhstan as Marcel Granollers
and Marc Lopez beat Evgeny Korolev and Yuriy Schukin in straight
sets. The  Czech Republic  beat Italy and Argentina defeated
Germany in doubles to also take 3-0 leads that clinched their
series.  Sweden beat Serbia and Russia defeated Austria to avoid
elimination as Croatia took a 2-1 lead over  Japan . Canada and
France are tied 1-1 going to their doubles match later today.
The first round ends tomorrow with two reverse singles matches
in each series.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
